result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 11:05 pm cases called. 14CM522, 15CF31, & 15CM295. Defendant Billy Joe Davis in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record by ADA Anderson. Attorney Zamzow concurs.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Counts 1-10 of 14CM522.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads in Counts 11-16 in 14CM522, 15CF31 & 15CM295. No statement by the defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 3 years. CONDITIONS:Count 1- 106 days WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit. Credit for 106 days served. No Contact with Dorothy Paczesny and/or Larry Hutton. Defendant is not to issue any checks at all. Defendant is not to be in possession of a checking account-unless the account is that of a Rep Payee for the defendant. Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Restitution in the amount of $5,583.83 (14CM522-$2,695.62, 15CM295-$140.51 & 15CF31-$2,747.75). Restitution to be paid in increments of no less than $150 per month starting January 5, 2016 and by the 5th of each month until paid in full. Lock & Load costs of $940.00. DNA Surcharge.  Appeal Rights Given.
from Atty Jeanne Zamzow, Dated 10/22/2015 Re: Request to Reschedule 10/27/2015 P/S due to conflict - Court grants request

1:15 pm cases called. 14CM522, 15CF31, & 15CM295. Defendant Billy Joe Davis in court with attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow.  Steven Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.    NGP entered on 14CM522 & 15CM295. Preliminary hearing and time limits discussed on 15CF31.  Preliminary hearing waived by the defendant. Court questions defendant and accepts waiver of right to preliminary hearing. Court finds probable cause and enters an order binding the defendant over for trial.  Information filed.  Attorney Zamzow confirms receipt and waives formal reading and enters a plea of NG.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.

BOND APPLICABLE TO CASE NOS. 14CM522, 15CF31 & 15CM295.   Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment or maintaining any open checking accounts. Defendant is prohibited from leaving the State of Wisconsin. Defendant to maintain a current address w/ the Clerk of Courts Office.

15CF31, 15CM295 & 14CM522 Cases called @ 1:31 p.m. Defendant Billy Joe Davis in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. ADA Anderson requesting $6000 Cash Bond. Atty Szilagyi takes no position on bond. Court orders $5500 Cash Bond. IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for September 2, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
